collections.description:
The Greedy Ape Heist is a deflationary collection of 6666 NFTs on the Solana Blockchain. Every Ape is completely unique! But not every Ape is here to stay…

Have you got what it takes to avoid ending up in THE SLAMMER?

The Slammer is where Apes end up when they get caught and removes them from circulation.

A portion of every secondary sale is added to The Slammer account and when there is a large enough amount, law enforcers roll through Solana marketplaces and lock up the cheapest Greedy Apes — “sweeping the floor.”

These Apes are taken out of circulation (“burned”), and the overall supply of Greedy Apes is reduced.

This is to reward diamond hand Ape hodlers by raising the floor price and reducing the supply, putting upward price pressure on all Greedy Ape NFTs. 

That's not all...

When you join the gang you will share a portion of the royalties. Every greedy ape you hold will grant you one share. The more you own the bigger your reward!

Are you ready to join the gang?

collections.description:
Today, the globe connects in more profound ways than ever before. At a time when people may feel the most lost and alone, we are confronting the injustices that wear us down.
Being online in a global village makes the world that much smaller, allowing some people to connect on the issues that matter most. Being truly disconnected for the first time has pushed us to reconnect with renewed purpose.
Individuals rise to fight for racial justice, closing class disparities, LGBTQ+ acceptance, environmental justice, and human rights everywhere. This was the year to make a change. Problems that once were swept under the rug could no longer be ignored. The status quo was disrupted. Most lives changed overnight, and many people felt they had nothing left to lose. The fight for justice is universal where global populations see with more clarity the intersections of race, class, gender, geography, and sexual expression, and accept that oppressed people must unite and fight in solidarity in order to win.
The damages didn’t go unnoticed. The images reveal that the sacrifices made during these fights affected all those who seek justice. Though the world is not saved, and justice is not achieved overnight, it’s clear that the fire will burn on for years to come. Being alone forces us to confront our own biases. Distancing Together is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Andrii Omelnytskyi, Eric Yain Setten, Gerry Bueno, Giuseppe Lombardo, Gussy Lowenhielm, Jamiul Adnan, Marta Novikova, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Nihal Raj, Roberto Juayan, Sergey Trush, Shrinkhla Srivastava, Steven Roe, Thomas Asteriades, Xavier Minguella Minguella, Артём Федоров
collections.name: Distancing Together

collections.description: The younger generation understands that, in the face of one of the greatest obstacles of time, they have a voice in the fight against systems that don't work for them. Many future leaders have been born, as great injustices increasingly are brought to light. They creatively find ways of expression through online and physical activism. The children in these images show us that there is a future worth fighting for. They show us that their generation deeply cares about the planet and all human life and that not much can stand in their way. They give hope. Future Leaders is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Alejandro Jaramillo, Alessandro Zarotti, Fernando Gonzalez-Criado Leyra, Giuseppe Lombardo, Haitham Dinnawi, Iris Savoy, Jason Little, Jason Segarra, Jun Pinzon, Laurentiu Vlad, Luca Votta, Martin Greene, Mougabé Saint Louis, Reinis Freilibs, Ruston Clyne, Simon Bond, Thomas Asteriades
collections.name: Future Leaders

collections.description: Our fights had a cost. All around the globe, the tragedies are both evident and subtle. Photos show the rubble, the hurt, the pollution, and the indescribable loss. We may not even know the full extent of these tragedies or even comprehend what has happened to others. It is important to remember that healing takes place, even when we are most weakened. These images remind us that no matter how bad the damages are that we sustain, there is always hope that we will come together again. Photography sheds light on the extent of the damages and attempts to capture the emotional cost. The Damages is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: adel hwajre, Ain Media, Antoni Mantorski, arimacs wilander, Bruno Dias, Haitham Dinnawi, imam buhori ibe , Mario Scharff, Oke Oluwasegun, Rouzbeh Fouladi, Zeina Kassem
collections.name: The Damages

collections.description: A raised fist is a universal symbol of power, solidarity, and a desire for change. Our photographers capture this universal gesture all across the globe, in all different contexts, whether it is a fist raised for Black Power, for a cause unique to a community, or in celebration. The fist has become a symbol uniting people throughout the year in a universal language of strength and togetherness. Raise up! Raise Your Fist To... is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Alessandro Zarotti, Ali Mousavi, Antoni Mantorski, Corinthia Croom, daniel samray, Egide Mbabazi, Emery Barnes, Haitham Dinnawi, imam buhori ibe , Jason Segarra, Joel Cadet, Jordan Scott, Jude Lartey, Kyaunna Hall, Laurentiu Vlad, Lisa Voinea, Mario Daye, Martin Greene, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Mougabé Saint Louis, Nicolas Barraza Jr, Nour Chamoun, Olivia Cadwell, Raekia Osgood, Reinis Freilibs, Rodescu Hopkins, Sax Eno, Simi Vijay, Thomas Asteriades, Toya Masri, Valentina Oyon, Zeina Kassem
collections.name: Raise Your Fist To...

collections.description: Even though our mouths could not be seen through our masks, our words are louder than ever. The images included show the signs that packed streets all over the world. This is what the people have to say. The signs come in all different forms, in different places, with different messages, but their purpose is consistent: changing the status quo. Signs of Change is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Alejandro Jaramillo, Anne D, Brian Otieno, Byeong Uk Cho, Dante  Diosina Jr, Edo Ardzenadze, Egide Mbabazi, Fredrick Osadare, Joseph Philip Angeles, Jun Pinzon, Lucas Lorizio, Marco Maisano, Natnael Tadesse, Patrick Busslinger, Sebastian Japson, Xavier Minguella Minguella
collections.name: Signs of Change

collections.description: Having to be away from everyone else is bringing us so much closer. In our bubbles, we reinforce the bonds we already had and experiment with new ways of being together. Love reinvented itself and has taken on all shapes and forms. Whether it is the love we feel at home when surrounded by our friends and families, or the warm glow of a video call from a long-distance friend who puts in the extra effort to show us they care—the solidarity of a companion, just you and them against the world. Love and Togetherness is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: adel hwajre, alessandro  castiglioni, Annabelle Farrugia, arimacs wilander, Aslı Gönen, Bernardo Ramonfaur, Bruno Dias, Daria Buriakova, Delicia Waller, Emery Barnes, Fernando Gonzalez-Criado Leyra, Fredrick Osadare, Giuseppe Lombardo, Godiva Omoruyi, Henri Fitriadi, Jamiul Adnan, Keziah Holman, Navid Mehedi Al Arefin, Pal Szilagyi Palko, Quiony Navarro, Sander Dalhuisen, Toya Masri, Yasir Taher
collections.name: Love and Togetherness

collections.name: Crypto Bull Club

collections.description: If the COVID 19 pandemic had happened twenty years ago, what would have been different? There are many ways to answer that, but what stands out about this era is our expanded reliance on the virtual. Systems are crashing and are overloaded as usage suddenly skyrockets to previously unimaginable numbers. The images in this category show that whether you were a seasoned pro at freelancing from home, attending your first online class, or just figuring out how to call your grandkids using your computer, nobody could avoid what was inevitable. The idea of a complete shift to online communication was predicted to happen eventually, of course. Little did we know that over the course of this period we would all quickly become faithful citizens of the global online village and, well... CREATE A NEW WORLD! What is next? Virtual Living is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: AHTISHAM MUNIR, alessandro  castiglioni, Bumi SEO, Creative Lab, Elias Herter, Giorgia Frare, Iyiola Olaniyan, Kristyna Hessova, Madhu Raj pandey, Slaven Orsolic, Tommaso Novi, Tom Shu, 月 汪
collections.name: Virtual Living

collections.description: At each new year, we typically make a promise to change up our lifestyle. Today it seems as if many people are taken aback by just how much their lives are transforming, as normalcy quickly became irrelevant. Physical changes are apparent as everyone navigates life under lockdown. Masks hang right at the door along with the keys to our houses, friends stay six feet away, and being a homebody suddenly seems like the only way to be. Lockdown lifestyle was unexpected, but adaptation is a must. Lockdown Lifestyle is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Abhay Patel, Abhijath Udayamvely, Akash Gayakwad, Alessandro Castiglioni, Antony Robinson, Antony Trivet, Arimacs Wilander, Bill Mok, Carlos Albertosi, Dante  Diosina Jr, David Gray, Diego Ibarra, Félix López, Hader Farghaly, Hanny Hsian, Harry Pham, Ibrahim Chowdhury, Ionny Dub, Iyiola Olaniyan, Joel Cadet, Josh Joshua, Juan Algar Carrascosa, Jun Pinzon, Khairul Amin, leonardo Savaris, Lou Morris, Maksim Chernyshev, Michael Williams Astwood, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Nicolaus Bonaventura, Niklas Soestmeyer, Nour Chamoun, Paolo Barretta, Pavel Musinszkij, Sebastian Japson, Serdar Göksu, Steve Bessas, Steven Roe, Suparerg Suksai, VALERIA JARAMILLO, Wing Yi Tai, Евгений Шухман
collections.name: Lockdown Lifestyle

collections.description:
One of the biggest shocks that the pandemic brought most people is the necessity of social distancing, which tears many families and communities apart away from the socially connected life we knew into an unfamiliar form of isolation. For a lot of communities and cultures, this new way of
life is especially difficult to accept. Physical touch is a main form of communication, where love, respect, and acknowledgment are typically shown through simple gestures that have become taboo overnight. Social Distancing is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Arimacs Wilander, Blake  McLemore, Dante  Diosina Jr, Fernando Gonzalez-Criado Leyra, Frederic Chen, Giuseppe Anello, Giuseppe Lombardo, Marcelo Colmenero, Marco Maisano, Simon Bond, Tracey Colley, Valentina Oyon, Xavier Minguella
collections.name: Social Distancing

collections.description: This is an ode to our heroes, all the professionals and volunteers working during the pandemic, and the ways in which we celebrate them. The essential workers are everyone’s heroes. When times get most uncertain, when it seems like life could be on the line, our hidden heroes do not stop. They make sacrifices, and they do it for the future of humanity. This pandemic may be one of the most defining battles of our generation, and it is a battle fought behind closed doors. Images can never fully capture all the ways our heroes fight. Yet even though their work often goes unnoticed, these heroes still carry on, as they do, as they will continue to do. Hidden Heroes is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Adel Hwajre, Akash Gayakwad, Alessandro  Castiglioni, Alex Gonzalez , Arimacs Wilander, Bernardo Ramonfaur, Bruno Dias, Dante  Diosina Jr, Egide Mbabazi, Hanny Hsian, Israel  Martínez Valdés, Jason Segarra, Jordan Scott, Lutfi Hanafi, Quiony Navarro, Xavier Minguella
collections.name: Hidden Heroes

collections.description: Photos capture how things may have looked, but there are few ways to describe the eeriness of the abandoned places the world has been feeling, with widespread lockdowns and social distancing in full effect. Millions of people see what once were bustling squares, streets, and public spaces. They have become empty. Essential workers have put their lives at risk to serve the rest of the population. Can we stay home? Until all public spaces can safely be occupied again, emptiness is a reminder of how far the world is from returning to normalcy. Empty Spaces is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Abhijath Udayamvely, Ahmad Sujono, Anujith Rajasekharan, Aslı Gönen, Bea Davidson, Devin Dabney, Hader Farghaly, Jamiul Adnan, Jose de Lago, Karthik GL, Kayque Andrade, Kedar Diwakar Mandakhalikar, Kentaro Watanabe, Mariyah Shahrin, Marko Zoric, Matt Doheny, Michael Sykes, Michalakis Ppalis, Mohamed Elgammal, Nagat Elsayed, Nelson Martínez, Omar Maher, Paolo Barretta, Rajdeep Chowdhury, Roberto Moreno, Sheng-En Chen, Stefan Magyar, Steven Roe, Takuma Enomoto, Tino Lehmann, Tom Weighton, Vanessa Tamarit, Victor Prevot, Viktorija Saulyte, Wing Yi Tai, Xavier Minguella
collections.name: Empty Spaces

collections.description: The world has turned upside down. The sudden shift to a population experiencing a rampant pandemic is jarring and shocking. These photos depict the nostalgia that we feel. The World Before is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Abhay  Patel, Abhijath Udayamvely, Alejandro Quintanilla, Alex Righetti, Andrej Mitin, Azim Khan Ronnie, Bruno Dias, Hader Farghaly, Hamid Noer, Jamiul Adnan, Lisa Voinea, Lois Laylo, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Muhammad Chaidir Umam, Simon Bond, Steven Roe, Taseer Ali, Victoria Seck, Wing Yi Tai
collections.name: The World Before

collections.description:
Although it was not the same for everyone, we all experienced isolation in the past few years. Everyday life as we knew it was completely transformed.
The images included in this part show the fear, the hesitation, even the excitement that this new way of life ushered in.  A lot of us picked up new hobbies at home and discovered interests we never knew we had as we felt more and more alone in our journeys.
These images are snapshots of inner workings. What was going on inside people’s heads? The collective trauma being experienced took its hold in unique ways. People showed their care for their loved ones in new ways. They mourned and grieved for those lost as well as for the lives they were missing out on.
The images that came pouring in from all around the world showed the array of locations, ages, genders, races, and classes that illustrated the vastness of the human experience. Although we were all far apart from one another, miraculously people found ways to stay more connected than ever.
We relied on one another in these dark times and used our latest tools to do so. The human tendency to stay together did not go away during the pandemic; it took on new shapes and forms. Isolation is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Albina Krasniqi, Aslı Gönen, David Rubin, Diana Samson, Evgenia Zhivaleva, Gairah Praskovia, Marcus Peña, Marta Novikova, Quiony Navarro, Siddharth Hirpara, Simone Martelli, Vikar Syed
collections.name: The Isolation

collections.description: People want to express themselves, many are unlocking their inner child and feeling experimental. Creativity helps get people through the inescapable boredom. These images reveal how people express themselves and get creative, we show each other the new hobbies we picked up, and we go out of our comfort zone in ways we never have before. Creativity Unleashed is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: Aslı Gönen, Benjamin Cantini, brijith vijayan, Dan Moga, Dennis Ingara, Jaine Neris, Jude Lartey, Kedar Diwakar Mandakhalikar, Lucas Lorizio, Mariya Bulba, Mathieu van den Berk, Michael Williams Astwood, Michail Nevradakis, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Rifkat Kakaev, Samuel Ubani, Steven Roe
collections.name: Creativity Unleashed

collections.description: When staring directly into the face of all the injustices threatening their lives, our communities, and all humanity, chose to fight back. These images capture only a fraction of the feelings experienced during that choice made to rise up. The pure energy, emotion, and anger had been building and building, only to finally release. All across the world, this same strong current is felt, empowering people to make their voices heard, whatever the consequences. Breaking Point is a collection of photos that is premiering in collaboration with Scopio, and the following global artists: adel hwajre, Alejandro Jaramillo, Ayorinde Ogundele, daniel samray, Jason Little, Jason Segarra, Laurentiu Vlad, Luciano Aenishanslins, Mikhail Grebenshchikov, Mougabé Saint Louis, Nour Chamoun, Simon Bond, Thomas Asteriades, Zeina Kassem
collections.name: The Breaking Point

collections.description:
A series of 200 generative pieces showcasing neural networks’ ability to replicate the Bouba/Kiki Effect: a phenomenon of non-arbitrary mental mapping between speech sounds & visual forms, discovered by Wolfgang Kohler in 1929. A German psychologist, Wolfgang put two images before a group of people from a variety of languages and cultures: one spiky, one round and blobby. 

"Which one is named kiki, which one bouba?" he asked them. 96% of them answered the spiky one is kiki and the round, blobby one is bouba.

collections.description:
Welcome to the Neopets Metaverse, a free-to-play, play-and-earn, community-driven game based on the original Neopets classic. Whether through exciting mini-games, thrilling PvP and PvE combat, or the unique Neopet care and customization system, the Neopets Metaverse offers both a nostalgic yet fresh Web3 gameplay experience for veteran Neopians and newcomers alike.

Neopets is best known for its classic browser game http://Neopets.com, which has cultivated memories for more than 150 million players. Neopians have immersed themselves in a vibrant world that represents more than a game: it’s an inclusive, welcoming online community that serves as a forum for expression and creativity.

In 2021 we decided to introduce this successful gaming IP to the blockchain ecosystem. We know how critical it is to bridge the nostalgia of traditional Neopets with the advent of Web3 so that these generational memories and impressions don’t get lost in translation. Are you ready to join us in the Neopets Metaverse?

Our project is focused on the beauty of art and the possibilities offered by blockchain and Solana to discover, share, value, and exchange it. We have a long-term goal of building a community of both artists and collectors that can experiment with emotional art.
On this page, you can find some pieces of our previous collections and our recently launched: Psychoanalysis.
Psychoanalysis (new collection): 1100 pieces called "Psyches" and numbered from 1 to 1100. This collection has been generated using generative adversarial networks, mixing different styles and genres to create unique and unrepeatable artworks. We've been carefully selecting art pieces that follow some styles that interlink very well together: synthetic and analytic cubism predominantly and then other complementary styles with less influence on the outcome. We would like each piece to be used as a personal Rorschach test, where each owner is able to look at it and initiate an introspective process that brings him closer to discovering something meaningful.
